Description: Solar energy is one of the most promising renewable energy sources.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Solar Energy Detroit is one of the most popular renewable energy sources in the world. Solar panels are devices that convert sunlight into electricity. They are made up of solar cells, which are made of silicon. Solar panels come in a variety of sizes and shapes, and they are usually black or dark blue. Solar panels are used to power homes, businesses, and cars. They can also be used to heat water and produce electricity. Solar panels are becoming more popular as the cost of renewable energy decreases and the awareness of the environmental benefits of solar energy increases. Solar panel technology has come a long way in recent years, and there are now more efficient and less expensive solar panels available. Solar panels are an excellent way to reduce your carbon footprint and save money on your energy bills. If you're looking for a solar panel installer in Detroit, Solar Energy Detroit is a great option. Solar Energy Detroit is a locally owned and operated business that specializes in solar panel installation and maintenance. Solar Energy Detroit has a team of experienced and certified solar panel installers who will work with you to find the best solar panel solution for your home or business. Solar Energy Detroit offers a free consultation to help you determine whether solar is right for you. Contact Solar Energy Detroit today to schedule your free consultation. Looking for a top-quality solar panel that will last for years and provide maximum energy output? Look no further than Solar Energy Detroit! Our solar panels are made with the highest quality materials and construction, so you can be assured they will withstand the harshest weather conditions and provide outstanding energy production year after year. Solar Energy Detroit solar panels are also backed by an industry-leading 25-year warranty, so you can rest easy knowing your investment is protected. And because we're passionate about making solar power more affordable for everyone, we offer incredible financing options to make going solar easier than ever. So why wait? Get started on your path to clean, renewable energy with Solar Energy Detroit today! When it comes to solar panels, many people in Michigan have one main concern: the long winter. However, there are actually quite a few sunny days throughout the year, and solar panels work best under cool, sunny conditions. On average, Michigan receives about 170 sunny days in a year. So although the winter may be long, the panels will still be able to generate power during those months. Plus, the panels retain their efficiency even during winter because good panels work best under cool, sunny conditions. So if you're looking for an environmentally-friendly and cost-effective way to power your home, solar energy is definitely worth considering.

Description: NumbersPay is a group buying service that offers goods at wholesale prices to individual consumers.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: NumbersPay is a group buying service that offers wholesale prices to individual consumers. We offer a range of products at significant discounts. Magic? Here's how we do it: Many retailers are willing to sell their products for lower-than-retail prices, but on one condition: they have to sell a lot of them. Unfortunately, most retailers don't know how to guarantee that they'll find enough buyers. Here's where we come in. At NumbersPay.com, we display a wide array of products from retailers at abnormally low prices. When you sign up as a NumbersPay user, you can pledge to purchase any of the products we show. For the deals to actually go through, we need a minimum number of pledges before the deal expires. When this happens, the retailers are happy, the deal is official and your order ships at the end of the time limit. If the minimum number of pledges isn't reached by the time limit, the deal is cancelled and you aren't charged a thing. But this is where it gets interesting. For many items, as the number of pledges grows we can continue to lower the prices they're offered at. Once the number of users pledging to buy an item reaches a bonus marker, its price drops by a certain percentage. Many of the items have multiple bonus deals, so by letting your friends know about NumbersPay and encouraging them to join, you can increase your chances of getting better and better deals. It boils down to this: the more people buying an item, the less it will cost. And we've integrated the site with online social networks to make sharing easier. Get the Deal Getting started is simple. Subscribe to our newsletter and follow us on Facebook or Twitter to start receiving notifications about our latest deals. Once subscribed you will be in the loop and be the first to find any of our products at groundbreaking prices.In order to continuously tailor our shopping experience to our users, we have the suggest a product survey that lets your input guide our next offers. Sign up for free and give it a try! Buy it! Find an item you're interested in? Simply click the Buy! button to make your pledge. Remember, only the minimum pledge quota needs to be met in order for the deal to go through. You won't be charged a dime if your deal doesn't go down! Share, Share, Share! The fun part for you and your wallet is sharing. In addition to prices going down as more users pledge to buy, our Refer & Save system actually gives you NumbersPay credit for getting your friends to sign up. Get a NumbersPay link connected to your own account at any time by clicking the Refer & Save button at the top of the page. Let the Good Prices Roll! Sit back, relax, and bask in the great deal you just received courtesy of NumbersPay. Don't forget to let us know what products you want next and we'll do the work to bring it right to your computer screen! With your help, we can continue to bring the prices you want.

Description: Desert Biker Magazine is a chronicle of the desert roads of the Southwestern United States and the motorcyclists who ride them.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, Inland Empire, West Coast
Full Description: Desert Biker Magazine is a chronicle of the desert roads of the Southwestern United States and the motorcyclists who ride them. A popular bi-monthly, 4-color  print magazine, Desert Biker Magazine has been in business for a year now and has published six magazines, each bigger and better than the one previous.  Their free publication features compelling, well-written stories and exceptional photography that has earned it a trusted reputation in the biker community. They've been repeatedly told it's the best looking magazine on the market and because they go so fast, they can't keep them stocked up at their major distribution points, primarily Harley, Indian and other motorcycle dealerships. They also hand out thousands to bikers at runs, rallies and other events throughout the southwestern desert region, allowing us to meet and converse with their readers, face to face.  Due to the quality of this publication, they've caught the eye of industry icons and are in talks with many of the motorcycle world's leading manufacturers  to provide an avenue of promotion for their products at a level beyond any they have advertised in before. Surprisingly, Desert Biker Magazine is a family business that consists of just two people who together handle production of the magazine, ad sales, subscriptions, business management and distribution. Due to the incredible demand for Desert Biker Magazine, and after a year of intense marketing, they are now at the stage of major expansion, meaning they need to increase distribution within and beyond their current Arizona, California and Nevada markets. That kind of expansion takes a great deal of capital in that printing and shipping costs are substantial and their biggest expense at this point.  It is their belief though, that those costs will very quickly be recovered by the increase in advertising revenue as they are more and more often approached by businesses that see the value of their product and understand the stability and wealth most biker possess.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment, Sales and Marketing
